Text.Value: Good for something, after all.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Player] push the corpse into lake after kneel inpect fail <LiliT>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The pushing of the corpse into the lake appears to be handled systemnically, so the camera can pan out and let animation take over.

Text.Value: Fine. Let's trade.
Then get your face outta mine.
It was a figure of speech, you lummox. We ain't looking for help.
Quit sniffin' around. You're starting to get on my nerves.
Done gawking? Lend a hand or get gone.
Where's your pickaxe, gnome? Thrinn know you're over here?
Attack.
Attack.
Are we.

EditorData.NodeContext: Said matter-of-factly and threateningly, about to start combat.

Text.Value: That's about the best end you can expect if you don't turn to the Absolute.
Gather yourself to strike.
Run 'em.

EditorData.NodeContext: Said as a threat, since htis is about ot start combat.

Text.Value: Lend a hand.
Grim work. Did you kill them?
Whoa, not so fast. Let's get the lay of the land before we settle on the scorched earth routine.
I've heard of many burial rites and last wishes in my time. Being tossed into fetid water is not one of them.
You know - I don't think she did. I think you're trying to escape. We aren't gonna let that happen, are we, Viss?
My friend, I play Goliath Goatball, Moon Hockey, and Pegasus Polo with corpses.
I'll finish up here. You're wanted with the others.
Hold up, ya rat - I asked you a question. Thrinn know you're sniffing around?
The half that weren't crushed are digging the True Soul outta the wreckage.
Tidy. Hope you enjoy a bit of tat, you dolt.
We've work to do. Stuff your Pegasus where the rainbow don't shine.
Nah. Rockfall smashed 'em. Can't have them stinking up the place.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player reaches for the trinket and lifts it off the corpse, stashing it into their inventory behind the back.

Text.Value: *Spits.*
I've been sent to help.
There's a time and a place for violence. I mean - this place is perfect, but is it the time?
Thank the Absolute. They're all yours.
Reach for the trinket.
Stay your hand - for now.
At least try to find out something of use before you kill them.

EditorData.NodeContext: 'violence doesn't always have to be the first option, you know'

Text.Value: She asked me to inspect the bodies for anything useful.
Something caught your eye, eh? That's grand. I'd be willing to let you take it, too, for a mere pittance.
Leave.
Leave.
Nerves.
Shit.
Hey, what're you - oh, I get it.
Leave.
Sod off, chum. I put more back in and I'm likely to break it.
Inspect the corpses.
Attack.
Stay your hand - for now.
Urgh. Hate being taken all literal-like by fancy types like you.
Absolute.
Ain't looking for company neither. Take a walk - go find yerself a minotaur to wrestle or something.
At ease. Observe, and learn. Once you are assured victory, then you strike.
Thrinn don't believe in mixing work between us and you. No, I think you were trying to escape.
I think not.
*Spits.*

EditorData.NodeContext: He spits on the ground, glowering.

Text.Value: Do what you can, then. Probably ain't much.
I hope you're checking them for loot first?
What do we do with runaways, Viss?
Well?
Too bad. Offer's expired.
Ooh, are we killing slavers? Me first!
Go on - get it done. You've got me at your side.

EditorData.NodeContext: In a low voice. Said to player, doesn't want others to hear.

Text.Value: *You reach for the trinket, but it's already gone.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player crouches and reaches for the corpse, but the trinket has already been taken by another player.
EditorData.VFXTags: Slight Sparkle from trinket then fade

Text.Value: This ain't no funeral - this is taking out the rubbish. They served their purpose, and now they're fish food.
*For a moment you thought you'd seen something shining on one of the corpses. Suddenly, it's vanished.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: This is for the edge case in which someone steals the trinket in the space of 1 node. Probably will work best as another shot of the corpse, sans glittering metal.

Text.Value: Hmph.
Sounds like a lark. I reckon I could kick a corpse farther than you.
'Less you're here to kick some stiffs lake-side, I suggest you bugger off.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Camera first pans acros the field of dead, then focuses on the duergar

Text.Value: You gotta be kidding. These trash don't have nothing on 'em but rocks.
I don't have the coin.
*You spot a shiny trinket on one of the corpses.*
Rocks.
Get gone.
Get on with it then, and keep quiet.
Put your back into it. Lazy bastards.
I ain't goin' 'til Thrinn tells me to go.

Synopsis: Two grouchy duergar, one a talker and one who somewhat mimics/ repeats what his partner says, are responsible for dumping dead gnome bodies into the lake. You can convince them to let you loot the bodies.
